dialogue: Hi Yin! My name is Frosty :penguin: and I’m here to help you learn all about science:microscope:, verbal reasoning (GRE) :input_latin_uppercase:, and safety:hammer_and_wrench:!
I ask you questions, and you give me answers.
We will learn fun things together!
Cool! Here's some questions on the GRE!
Let's see if you can get this one.
Remember that you can always type in you answer and I'll help you to evaluate it :smiling_face_with_smiling_eyes:

Although John F. Kennedy was known for his carefree flag football games, Gerald Ford should be _____ as our football president: he turned down offers to play for two National Football League teams in order to pursue a career in public service.
